About 3 years ago I started having very intense visions and dreams of what seemed to be a potential future life for me. The visions were very beautiful and satisfying and gave me a lot of hope especially when I first started having them. But as the time went by all throughtout 2017 which was extremelly heavy and challenging year, hope was replaced by frustration. I couldn't understand why I kept having these amazing visions while struggling so much. Nothing was going right at that time yet every time I'd close my eyes to meditate, or before falling asleep, these beautiful, positive, exciting visions would appear, like happy movies playing out on my mental screen. Images I was receiving were polar opposite of what I was going through and it made me angry, I felt that I was either given a false hope or that some unseen force is making fun of me. I just couldn't believe anything good could come out a difficult place I was in. Yet, despite my frustration, anger and confusion I kept having those happy visions throughout 2018 and early 2019. Then they stopped and I thought: "Good, that was some cruel cosmic joke anyway." I kept living my life, trying to better myself and heal and let it all go. Little by little things started to change and I felt some amazing shifts and got to a place where I'm actually healthy, happy and feel whole and fullfilled. I stopped caring whether those persistent visions were false hope or potential future, I knew I'm okay either way, all is well. But guess what, as of recently, visions I've had back in 2016. HAVE started to manifest. What once seemed impossible is happening now (ironically I'd be ok if it didn't happen too). So I wanted to say to anyone who still might be struggling not to dismiss their visions, dreams, glimpes of future happiness and joy. Just because something didn't happen yet, it doesn't mean it never will, it takes time for us to heal, to recover, to become ready to receive our blessings. Keep going and keep the faith! üí™üß°
